go_data.justification: SNARE proteins are key regulators of docking and fusion of intracellular membranes.
SNARE proteins control membrane fusion, including the fusion of vesicles with the plasma membrane during exocytosis.
SNARE proteins, including SNAP-25 and syntaxin 13, have been implicated in neurite outgrowth.
SNARE proteins are key regulators of docking and fusion of intracellular membranes, including vesicle fusion.
SNARE proteins assemble into heterotypic complexes containing one domain each of the Qa, Qb, Qc and R types.
